<ns2091:section xmlns:ns2091="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2ee.ejb.enterpriseBeans.sessionBeans.stateless.beanImplementation.lifeCycleServices">

  <ns2092:title xmlns:ns2092="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Life cycle services</ns2092:title>
  <ns2093:para xmlns:ns2093="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    The bean implementation must provide an <ns2094:literal xmlns:ns2094="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ejbCreate</ns2094:literal> method for each
    <ns2095:literal xmlns:ns2095="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">create</ns2095:literal> method in the home interface. Similarly there must be an
    <ns2096:literal xmlns:ns2096="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ejbRemove</ns2096:literal> method as well as <ns2097:literal xmlns:ns2097="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ejbActivate</ns2097:literal> and
    <ns2098:literal xmlns:ns2098="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">ejbPassivate</ns2098:literal> methods. If there are no special tasks to be performed on
    creation, removal, activation and passivation, then we can simply supply empty bodies for each
    one of these.
  </ns2093:para>
</ns2091:section>